{
  "stem": "4963.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was, from what I understand, the Lithuanian, the Jewish population really had-- was the enlightenment of Europe in-- for the Jews in, in Kovno, especially-- or in Lithuania, there were many yeshivas.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were many Jewish printings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Yiddish in Lithuania was the literary Yiddish, many learned people and, and rabbis.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were very, very rough and very vengeful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They immediately-- when we were placed into the ghetto, they immediately vandalized all the homes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] most of-- I wouldn't say all the Lithuanians, but most of the Lithuanians were really cold-blooded murderers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Many of them were really-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] felt very badly about it and, and would come over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember they would come to the barbed wires, and they would start trading with us and, and bringing us food and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we, we made-- the only way you could go out of the ghetto was in a working force.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so they used to take them out as laborers, hard laborers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they would go out in the morning, and then they'd come back in the evening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and so the Lithuanians would come over to the workforce and especially to trade, you know, for goods and valuables.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, you know, some of them would, would send letters with the, with, with people, say do you know so and so, and please give them this letter, you know, and sympathy and so on and asking them if they could help in any way.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't because I was only 11.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so I was not-- I could not go out to work.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
